Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.69,0:00:13.32,Magus-Episode_Title,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1500,1500)}Those Awaiting a Star\N {\fs20}Part 2
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.44,0:00:18.33,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the library of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.32,0:00:22.15,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.15,0:00:23.25,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.00,0:00:26.89,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the magician of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.30,0:00:30.08,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,No, hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:32.59,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, that's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.59,0:00:36.36,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just trying to make \Nyou feel comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:41.96,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys won't come inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.59,0:00:45.31,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You can see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.04,0:00:47.16,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.16,0:00:48.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.67,0:00:52.39,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell me why{\i1} you {\i0}can see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.29,0:00:57.86,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, none of the wicked \Nones can get in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.24,0:01:00.32,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, I don't let them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:07.27,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's busy with their books.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.75,0:01:09.47,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,No one's going to hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.36,0:01:11.79,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You do understand, I hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.54,0:01:16.38,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat. Make yourself at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.05,0:01:22.30,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see if I have a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.75,0:01:26.22,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a very long time \Nsince anyone's come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.59,0:01:29.88,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.92,0:01:36.28,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I have a book you might like.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.77,0:01:42.08,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Or, should I say, a book that likes you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.90,0:01:49.35,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.48,0:01:53.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for barging in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.70,0:01:55.70,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.05,0:01:59.96,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.94,0:02:05.38,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a second, just a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.16,0:02:07.49,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.49,0:02:08.92,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,It should be here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.92,0:02:10.07,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,This'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:12.61,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:14.12,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.12,0:02:15.44,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Miura Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.93,0:02:17.75,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:20.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.83,0:02:22.27,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.29,0:02:25.73,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,That's a beautiful name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.92,0:02:29.74,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.48,0:02:33.75,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Your library card.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.36,0:02:35.66,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,It's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.43,0:02:39.92,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to need it to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.92,0:02:41.29,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.12,0:02:45.29,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.29,0:02:48.00,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to run straight through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:49.60,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Now, run.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.17,0:03:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.42,0:03:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.04,0:03:11.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you put your phone down \Nwhen someone's talking to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.83,0:03:13.07,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.07,0:03:14.00,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:15.15,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I said wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.15,0:03:16.49,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You always say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.50,0:03:18.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You never listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.46,0:03:19.20,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:21.71,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what I go through every day?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.71,0:03:22.70,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:23.72,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No, you don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.01,0:03:28.35,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired, too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:29.60,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the girl, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:32.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one taking care of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.57,0:03:35.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who took \Nher in just to be nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.12,0:03:36.17,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Well, so did you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.17,0:03:37.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:56.73,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.73,0:03:58.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.03,0:04:00.75,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Daiki, hurry up and get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:09.21,Default,Daiki,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.57,0:04:11.68,Default,Daiki,0000,0000,0000,,Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:15.18,Default,Daiki,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault that Mom's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.66,0:04:48.40,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.40,0:04:49.59,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.69,0:04:59.28,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:34.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:04.48,sign_10124_75__Book_Report,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Book Report
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.85,0:07:18.11,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:22.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,May I read some books?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:23.99,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:26.13,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You have your library card, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.54,0:07:30.85,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.85,0:07:35.47,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,as long as you have this card, \Nyou're a member here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.47,0:07:39.02,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You can come whenever you want, \Nand you can borrow the books.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:41.06,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Only one at a time, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.46,0:07:44.98,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And you must never leave the front door open.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.51,0:07:49.27,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Mind those rules, and you can \Ncome here every day, if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.27,0:07:50.49,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Every day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.14,0:08:01.11,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.11,0:08:02.17,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.34,0:08:10.58,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,As often as you like, as long as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.93,0:08:17.75,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Hatori-san, \Nto the library of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:37.07,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:49.06,sign_13829_92_Bees,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1500,1500)}Bees
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.44,0:10:20.59,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,No, we can't deal with her anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.27,0:10:22.53,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.53,0:10:25.34,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,My wife left with the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:28.21,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,We've done enough for her, haven't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.21,0:10:29.97,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn to take her, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.89,0:10:50.22,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You're a real bookworm now, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.22,0:10:51.00,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:55.16,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can forget all my problems \Nwhile I'm reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:57.04,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:11:00.50,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori-san, if you'd like, \Nwhy don't you stay—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.50,0:11:01.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.34,0:11:04.67,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.67,0:11:09.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't decide which one\N to do my book report on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.27,0:11:12.49,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Even after you've read so many?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.49,0:11:15.22,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I liked all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.18,0:11:17.23,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.68,0:11:20.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What's that book like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:22.38,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,That one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.40,0:11:25.62,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.18,0:11:27.91,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's always there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:32.19,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,That one, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.80,0:11:37.17,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,What was that book like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:42.34,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Which one should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.03,0:11:44.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:54.44,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I love reading the last page \Nof a book more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:18.17,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,How could this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.51,0:12:20.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.25,0:12:24.39,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You have to leave for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:28.19,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.19,0:12:28.84,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.42,0:12:41.81,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.81,0:12:42.82,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.66,0:12:45.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,My book report.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:46.52,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.54,0:12:49.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.42,0:13:01.50,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Won't your mom be worried if \Nyou don't come home soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:05.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No one worries about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:07.57,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:10.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Auntie left home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.45,0:13:13.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's all my fault, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.57,0:13:15.33,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I keep noticing the weird things,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.33,0:13:18.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,and it makes Auntie angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.36,0:13:30.72,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Just this once.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:33.59,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Just today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.80,0:13:38.78,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Let's find a book for your report.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.87,0:13:57.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I just really didn't want \Nto go home that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.16,0:13:59.80,Default,Magus,0000,0000,0000,,That's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.80,0:14:02.15,Default,Magus,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd be so insistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.08,0:14:04.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.50,0:14:08.84,Default,Ruth,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.84,0:14:10.74,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.74,0:14:12.26,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:14.86,Default,Ruth,0000,0000,0000,,As long as this isn't hard on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.36,0:14:16.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And then? And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:21.99,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,And that became a special night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:04.94,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,There's a book I want you to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.60,0:15:15.49,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,"The Lonely Little Star."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.81,0:15:20.81,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A picture book?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.18,0:15:27.08,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling you really need this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.58,0:15:32.04,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Now, will you clean up these books for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:41.41,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.33,0:17:18.05,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,"The lonely little star, the tiny child of a star,\N twinkled in the empty sky all by itself."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.91,0:17:42.66,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send her home before sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.37,0:17:44.37,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.42,0:17:46.73,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.73,0:17:50.01,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never come back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.26,0:19:13.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.59,0:19:24.60,sign_27851_160_Flowers,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.30,0:19:31.22,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.29,0:19:38.06,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.44,0:19:40.44,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.79,0:19:44.54,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-sa—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.54,0:19:45.25,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.25,0:19:46.83,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,How did you get in?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.83,0:19:47.44,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.01,0:19:51.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:56.42,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You, the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.25,0:19:58.35,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.46,0:20:19.59,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.52,0:20:21.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Not this book!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.91,0:20:35.72,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:37.21,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.60,0:20:45.59,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:47.57,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.57,0:20:49.88,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.88,0:20:51.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.10,0:20:54.70,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.20,0:21:07.71,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.92,0:21:11.73,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.21,0:21:13.85,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll lend you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.86,0:21:18.25,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mayumi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:19.87,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Promise you'll give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.53,0:21:22.64,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.29,0:21:25.31,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.57,0:21:27.63,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:37.22,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.58,0:21:41.79,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Can you move?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.61,0:21:48.27,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.89,0:21:51.27,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,They're gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.54,0:21:53.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.12,0:21:55.38,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't close the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.38,0:21:58.95,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori Chise-san, I need you \Nto do something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.62,0:22:01.46,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Deliver it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:05.04,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.32,0:22:11.44,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.66,0:22:13.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.45,0:22:15.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.27,0:23:49.19,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A promise left unfulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.19,0:23:53.46,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The girl runs onward, holding \Nwith her a young man's regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.87,0:23:57.13,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Not knowing what she'll find...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.02,0:24:00.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-san.
